Using M20060629-1905

The Extract Interface refactoring is used on the following class "List" to create a new interface "IBag".

class List
{
  private List[] array = new List[1];
}

Once the refactoring is performed, the field declaration "array" is incorrectly updated to:

  private List[] Array = new IBag[1];

Leading to a type error.

This exception is thrown because EMF Resource of semantic model gives null ids for models elements.
To make copy/paste is needed

either all model elements have attributes with ID=true (in ecore model) and id attributes are correctly initialized

or following methods of EMF Resource of semantic model 
useIDAttributes() returns false and useUUIDs() returns true.
You can make own implementation for this methods in your resource:
protected boolean useIDAttributes() {
	return false;
}

protected boolean useUUIDs() {
	return true;
}
(this way works fine in my project)

In the Logic Diagram Editor example copy/paste works because semantic model elements are contained in GMFResource.
Methods of GMFResource useIDAttributes() returns false and useUUIDs() returns true.

Using M20060629-1905

If we use the Extract Interface refactoring on the following class "List" without selecting any member,

class List
{
  public void RemoveTail() {
  }
}

then, in the following class Test, the "for" construct is incorrectly updated.

class Test
{
  public static void main(String[] args)
  {
    List[] array = new List[10];
    for(List l : array)
    {
      l.RemoveTail();
    }
  }
}

After the refactoring we have:

class Test
{
  public static void main(String[] args)
  {
    IBag[] array = new IBag[10];
    for(IBag l : array)
    {
      l.RemoveTail();
    }
  }
}

But "l" does not contain a member RemoveTail.

